commitResults.messageTitle: Level-0: Rename chatbot and add greeting
Add Level 2 add the ability to store and display
Add Level-3 task management with mark/unmark functions
commitResults.messageBody:
Implemented the ability for users to mark tasks as done and unmark them
back to not done. Refactored task handling to use a separate Task class,
following the A-Classes extension. Updated main program to support:

* 'mark <number>' to mark a task as done
* 'unmark <number>' to mark a task as not done
* Safe handling of invalid indices to prevent crashes

commitResults.messageTitle: Add support for Level-4 tasks: Todo, Deadline, Event
commitResults.messageBody:
Introduce Todo, Deadline, and Event classes inheriting from Task to allow
tracking different types of tasks with appropriate attributes:

* Todo: task without date/time
* Deadline: task with a due date/time
* Event: task with start and end times

Update GoGoGoose to parse user commands for todo, deadline, and
event. Implement consistent output messages matching Duke Level-4
specifications.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor code to comply with Java coding standard

commitResults.messageBody:
Created helper methods to handle adding any type of Task.
This reduces duplicate code in Todo, Deadline, and Event handlers.

Benefits:
* Keeps taskCount increment consistent
* Consolidates printing task-added messages
* Improves readability and maintainability

commitResults.messageTitle: Teach the chatbot to deal with errors
Refactor deadline, event, mark/unmark, and todo commands to provide clearer and more precise feedback for invalid inputs.
commitResults.messageBody:
Changes:
* Deadline command: split input by "/by", trim description and date,
  and throw distinct GooseExceptions for missing description, missing /by date,
  or both missing.
* Event command: split input into description, /from start time, and /to end time,
  and validate each component with specific GooseExceptions.
* Unmark commands: check if task number is missing, non-numeric, or invalid,
  and provide precise error messages to avoid crashes.

This improves user experience by clearly indicating what part of the command
is invalid, reducing confusion and preventing invalid tasks from being added.
